= (ala)wiki =
== About ==
Alawiki is a simple and very fast WikiEngine (really faster than MediaWiki<ref>http://www.mediawiki.org</ref> and others).

=== Changes ===
; wiki-20100104.tgz
: bugfix: closing nowiki block corrected
: bugfix: cell alignment detection in the last cell corrected
: bugfix: reference numbering corrected
: bugfix: don't open a paragraphs in table cells
: bugfix: close pre tag before open new table row if necessary
: changed: Creole table works now in a MediaWiki table cell
: changed: formatting MediaWiki images via CSS and link to the image by default

; wiki-20100102.tgz
: bugfix: further HTML code generation cleanup
: bugfix: list code rewritten to generate valid HTML
: changed: use named anker instead id in headers

; wiki-20091231.tgz
: bugfix: generate valid HTML in nested lists
: bugfix: handle nested MediaWiki tables
: bugfix: cell alignment detection in tables
: changed: keep preformatted and tables in lists 
: bugfix: HTML code generation cleanup
: added: HTML & CSS validator links
: added: optional authorization prepared
: added: support for creole images, nowiki tag ~{~{~{ and escape character ~
: added: basic support for MediaWiki images and some image attributes
: added: support for MediaWiki nowiki tag

; wiki-20091229.tgz
: bugfix: parse wiki tags in preformated text with space at the beginning of the line
: bugfix: more special character translations
: bugfix: handle creole tables without ending | correctly
: bugfix: parse wiki tags in creole tables
: added: support for creole line break
: added: support to view, diff, edit and discard the draft file (when OPT["DRAFT_VIEW"] enabled)
: added: OPT["DOC_DIR"]

; wiki-20091227.tgz **(first release)**
: bugfix: save dosn't append new line on each row 
: bugfix: misc code cleanups
: added: support for MediaWiki compatible attributes on table rows <ref>[[http://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Tables#Attributes_on_rows]]</ref>, [[# Definition list|definition lists]] <ref>[[http://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Formatting#Text formatting markup]]</ref>
: added: support for creole & MediaWiki [[#Character formatting]]
: added: diff mode during editing
: changed: [[#cell alignment detection]] improved

; wiki-20091226a.tgz
: bugfix: handle numbered external links
: bugfix: handle simplest wiki markup table structure
: bugfix: check write permission before edit mode allowed
: added: support for creole tables <ref>http://www.wikicreole.org/wiki/Creole1.0#section-Creole1.0-Tables</ref>, horizontal rules <ref>http://www.wikicreole.org/wiki/Creole1.0#section-Creole1.0-HorizontalRule</ref>, line breaks <ref>http://www.wikicreole.org/wiki/Creole1.0#section-Creole1.0-LineBreaks</ref>
: changed: cells with numbers are right aligned by default

; wiki-20091226.tgz
